# Forbidden Practices

This rule defines practices that are strictly prohibited in this codebase.

## Quality
- **NO `print()`**: Use a logger instead.
  - *Bad*: `print('user login');`
  - *Good*: `log.info('user login');`
- **NO Magic Numbers/Strings**: Use constants.
  - *Bad*: `if (status == 1) ...`
  - *Good*: `if (status == UserStatus.active) ...`
- **NO Deep Nesting**: Return early to flatten code.
  - *Bad*:
    ```dart
    if (user != null) {
      if (user.isActive) {
        ...
      }
    }
    ```
  - *Good*:
    ```dart
    if (user == null) return;
    if (!user.isActive) return;
    ...
    ```

## API Integration
- **NO Hardcoded URLs**: Use environment variables or configuration files.
  - *Bad*: `http.get(Uri.parse('https://api.example.com/users'))`
  - *Good*: `http.get(Uri.parse('${Config.baseUrl}/users'))`
- **NO Synchronous HTTP**: All network calls must be async and handled properly.
- **Error Handling**: Always try-catch network requests.

## Git Workflow
- **NO Force Push on Main**: Reviewers must block this.

## Performance
- **NO Unnecessary Builds**: Extract widgets.
- **Use `const`**: Whenever possible.

